      <div class="editors-post-body repostus-body">
        <p>When one combines the words "authentic" and "Italian" in the same sentence, one is bound to get in trouble; each region, each town, each family has their <em>own</em> way, the <em>right</em> way. When it comes to pasta, the debates rage on. While we preach no <em>right</em> way here, we can preach a good way -- and here are ten good (no, great!) recipes for classic Italian pastas. How does your<em> nonna</em> make them? Let us know in the comments!</p>
<p><a href="/recipes/2676-linguine-con-vongole">Linguine con Vongole</a> by<a href="/users/333-thewimpyvegetarian"> TheWimpyVegetarian</a></p>
<p><a title="Linguine con Vongole" href="/recipes/2676-linguine-con-vongole"><img style="vertical-align: middle;" src="http://d2k9njawademcf.cloudfront.net/indeximages/27913/original/linguine_con_vongole.jpg?1345084755" alt="Linguine con Vongole" width="620" /></a></p>
